DUBAI FIRE took the lead nearing the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure approaching the quarter, was met at the rail nearing the head of the lane and remained a close factor through the upper stretch before flattening stride. SISYPHUS stalked the early pace off the rail, gave chase leaving the five eighths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and showed little more. RAINBOW DAY raced in the four path the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the six path and showed little more. DEE DEE SIX saved ground and showed little response. VIBRANT FORCE became anxious in the gate, raced well off the pace in the three path the opening turn and proved no factor. COOLKID raced in the five path the first turn and was through early.
